`target_path` | none | N |\\n104: | `target_profile` | Y | marker `target_profile`, or auto-detect from `target_path` (`handover` -> `handover`, `context-prime` -> `context-prime`, otherwise `dynamic`) | inferred from `target_path` | N |\\n105: | `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, or requires...\n  Line 53: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830239891,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4c8ffeCP0WGGT1eimWex\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_U83PfixxDBQzH71Xtos4Hfun\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md\",\"offset\":55,\"limit\":90},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-skill-benchmark-loop.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n55: \\n56: **Phase Output:**\\n57: - `general_agent_verified = ________________`\\n58: \\n59: ---\\n60: \\n61: ## Setup\\n62: \\n63: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED** — resolve ALL inputs below before the Run step. In `:confirm`/no-suffix, present the resolved inputs and wait for confirmation; in `:auto`, resolve confidently from arguments/defaults or fail fast naming the missing inputs. Do NOT run the loop-host command until inputs are resolved.\\n64: \\n65: Resolve:\\n66: - **target skill** — the skill id or root to benchmark (must have an `INTENT_SIGNALS` + `RESOURCE_MAP` smart router for Mode A; e.g. the `cli-*` skills).\\n67: - **outputs dir** — where `skill-benchmark-report.{json,md}` are written.\\n68: - **fixtures dir** (optional) — defaults to `<skill>/assets/skill-benchmark/fixtures/<skill-id>/`.\\n69: - **trace mode** — `router` (Mode A, deterministic, default/CI) or `live` (Mode B, BUILT — playbook corpus dispatched through `cli-opencode`).\\n70: \\n71: ## Run\\n72: \\n73: ```bash\\n74: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\\\\n75:   --mode=skill-benchmark \\\\\\n76:   --skill=<skill-id-or-root> \\\\\\n77:   --outputs-dir=<path> \\\\\\n78:   [--fixtures-dir=<path>] [--trace-mode=router] [--advisor-mode=python]\\n79: ```\\n80: \\n81: `--advisor-mode=python` enables the built-but-opt-in D1-inter advisor probe (deterministic in-repo SQLite advisor, scored out-of-band; off by default and in CI). The orchestrator (`scripts/skill-benchmark/run-sk...\n  Line 54: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830239928,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4c8ffeCP0WGGT1eimWex\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_svNKfiF1fWRjdUlAU3jsftFV\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/feature_catalog/01--frontier-seeding/config-shape-and-default-pool.md\",\"offset\":35,\"limit\":35},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/feature_catalog/01--frontier-seeding/config-shape-and-default-pool.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n35: | `loopType` | `\\\"context\\\"` | Fixed to `\\\"context\\\"` for this loop |\\n36: | `executionMode` | `\\\"auto\\\"` or `\\\"interactive\\\"` | From mode suffix |\\n37: | `maxIterations` | `8` | Maximum parallel sweep iterations |\\n38: | `convergenceThreshold` | `0.10` | Per-iteration new agreement-eligible findings floor |\\n39: | `relevanceGate` | `0.55` | Minimum per-finding relevance to survive the gate |\\n40: | `agreementMin` | `2` | Minimum distinct executors for agreement-eligible status |\\n41: | `fanout.mode` | `\\\"by-model-shared-scope\\\"` | Fixed; every seat sweeps the same focus |\\n42: | `fanout.concurrency` | `4` | CLI pool concurrency cap |\\n43: | `fanout.executors` | default pool | Executor pool array |\\n44: \\n45: ### Default Pool\\n46: \\n47: When no `--executor` / `--executors` flags or marker are present, the default heterogeneous pool is used: 2 native `@deep-context` Task seats + 1 MiMo-v2.5-pro seat (`cli-opencode`) + 1 gpt seat (`cli-codex`) + 1 deepseek-v4-pro seat (`cli-opencode`). All seats sweep the same focus and agreement is the confidence signal. A single-seat pool is legal but yields no agreement signal; the command warns and continues.\\n48: \\n49: ### Pool Precedence\\n50: \\n51: CLI flags and `--executors` JSON take precedence over the `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` marker block, which takes precedence over the config file default. The pool i...\n  Line 55: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830239967,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4c8ffeCP0WGGT1eimWex\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_7PV0iAhUNEzfweXAbBQopB3h\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/manual_testing_playbook/01--frontier-seeding/config-shape-and-default-pool.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":40},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/manual_testing_playbook/01--frontier-seeding/config-shape-and-default-pool.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: \\\"FS-003 -- Config Shape and Default Pool\\\"\\n3: description: \\\"This scenario validates Config Shape and Default Pool for `FS-003`. It focuses on the default config template fields and the default heterogeneous executor pool written during fresh initialization.\\\"\\n4: ---\\n5: \\n6: # FS-003 -- Config Shape and Default Pool\\n7: \\n8: This document captures the realistic user-testing contract, current behavior, execution flow, source anchors, and metadata for `FS-003`.\\n9: \\n10: ---\\n11: \\n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n13: \\n14: This scenario validates Config Shape and Default Pool for `FS-003`. It focuses on the `deep_context_config.json` template, the threshold defaults (`relevanceGate: 0.55`, `agreementMin: 2`, `maxIterations: 8`, `convergenceThreshold: 0.10`), the default heterogeneous pool (2 native + MiMo + gpt + deepseek), and the `fanout.mode: \\\"by-model-shared-scope\\\"` invariant.\\n15: \\n16: ### Why This Matters\\n17: \\n18: The config is treated as read-only after initialization. If the template is missing fields or threshold defaults diverge from what is documented in SKILL.md or the command's Default Resolution Table, operators will get unexpected convergence behavior. Aligning template, command defaults, and SKILL.md is the baseline correctness check for every future run.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\\n...\n  Line 56: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830239990,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4c8ffeCP0WGGT1eimWex\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_nN6AwgFaCh038JUAZuKHZ4UW\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\"offset\":190,\"limit\":20},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n190: > **Feature File:** [FS-002](01--frontier-seeding/scope-binding-and-code-graph-seeding.md)\\n191: \\n192: ---\\n193: \\n194: ### FS-003 | Config Shape and Default Pool\\n195: \\n196: #### Description\\n197: Verify that `step_create_config` writes the correct config fields from the `deep_context_config.json` template, including the default heterogeneous executor pool and all threshold defaults.\\n198: \\n199: #### Scenario Contract\\n200: Prompt: As a manual-testing orchestrator, validate the config shape and default pool contract for `deep-context` against the command entrypoint, auto YAML, asset template, and SKILL.md quick reference. Verify `deep_context_config.json` defines the default pool (2 native + MiMo + gpt + deepseek), `relevanceGate: 0.55`, `agreementMin: 2`, `maxIterations: 8`, `convergenceThreshold: 0.10`, and `fanout.mode: \\\"by-model-shared-scope\\\"`. Return a concise verdict.\\n201: \\n202: Expected signals: `assets/deep_context_config.json` is present with correct field names; SKILL.md §8 quick reference matches the config defaults; the command's default resolution table in `start-context-loop.md` aligns with the config template.\\n203: \\n204: Desired user-visible outcome: fresh sessions always produce a config file whose defaults match the documented thresholds and the default heterogeneous pool.\\n205: \\n206: #### Test Execution\\n207: > **Feature File:** [FS-003](01--frontier-s...\n  Line 59: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830251671,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4c8ffeCP0WGGT1eimWex\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_vNBcyWVII82sU6otFYS23Mlj\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"fail fast|fail-fast|:auto|AUTONOMOUS|required inputs|missing inputs|WAIT for user|DO NOT proceed\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 20 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md:\\n  Line 2: description: \\\"Benchmark a model or prompt framework: fixtures, pattern or 5dim scoring, deterministic or graded runs. :auto/:confirm.\\\"\\n\\n  Line 3: argument-hint: \\\"<profile_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--scorer=pattern|5dim] [--grader=noop|mock|llm] [--iterations=N] [--executor=NAME --model=NAME] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n\\n  Line 14: > 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\\n\\n  Line 66: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch