agent runtime mirrors, (006) native-only default executor pool, (007) Phase-0 @general + un-skippable setup hard-blocker gates on all 7 deep commands. The work is mostly markdown command/skill docs, agent definition files (.md / .toml), and a JSON config — so weight correctness, internal consistency, stale/contradictory wording, wrong tool/flag/model references, broken cross-references, and read-only-contract/security issues over classic runtime code bugs. Slice: review ONLY .opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md. Focus: native-default pool Q-Pool A/B wording, default-policy prose, PRE-BOUND marker examples, flag plumbing for --executor/--executors. Return JSON findings only.\",\"specFolder\":\"\",\"tenantId\":\"\",\"userId\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"\",\"limit\":3,\"session_id\":\"\",\"turnNumber\":1,\"include_cognitive\":false},\"output\":\"{\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Matched 3 memories via trigger phrases\\\",\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"matchType\\\": \\\"trigger-phrase\\\",\\n    \\\"count\\\": 3,\\n    \\\"results\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"memoryId\\\": 8550,\\n        \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/005-command-agent-alignment\\\",\\n        \\\"filePath\\\": \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/005-command-agent-alignment/spec.md\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Phase 5: Command & Agent Alignment [system-spec-kit/024-compact-code-graph/005-command-agent-alignment/spec]\\\",\\n        \\\"matchedPhrases\\\": [\\n          \\\"phase\\\",\\n     ...\n  Line 5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830110512,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"skill\",\"callID\":\"call_gqY0PuG9GvPSbhCTkqa70CsF\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"name\":\"sk-doc\"},\"output\":\"<skill_content name=\\\"sk-doc\\\">\\n# Skill: sk-doc\\n\\n<!-- Keywords: sk-doc, markdown-quality, skill-creation, document-validation, ascii-flowchart, llms-txt, content-optimization, extract-structure -->\\n\\n# Documentation Creation Specialist - Unified Markdown & Component Management\\n\\nUnified specialist providing: (1) Document quality pipeline with structure enforcement and content optimization, (2) OpenCode component creation (skills, agents, commands) with scaffolding, validation and packaging, (3) ASCII flowchart creation for visualizing workflows, (4) Install guide creation for setup documentation and (5) Feature catalog and manual testing playbook creation for inventory and validation packages.\\n\\n**Core Principle**: Structure first, then content, then quality.\\n\\n**Architecture**: Scripts handle deterministic parsing/metrics. AI handles quality judgment and recommendations.\\n\\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n\\n### Use Case: Document Quality Management\\n\\nEnforce markdown structure, optimize content for AI assistants, validate quality through script-assisted AI analysis.\\n\\n**README Creation** - Use `readme_template.md` + `readme_creation.md` when:\\n- Creating new README for any folder or project\\n- User requests \\\"create a README\\\", \\\"add documentation\\\", \\\"write a README\\\"\\n- Folder needs comprehensive documentation\\n- Workflow: [readme_creation.md](./references/readme_creation.md) | Template: [readme_template.md](./assets/readme/readme_template.md)\\n\\n**Skill README Creation** - Use `skill_readme_template.md` when:\\n- Creating or refreshing `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md`\\n- A skill README needs human-facing purpose, quick start, structure, examples, troubleshooting, FAQ or related-resource navigation\\n- Template: [skill_readme_temp...\n  Line 8: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830117157,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_tHcTW9hvjPVLfM5nePsY1YSp\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/miche