I seat) is a\\n21: #   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\\n22: #   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\\n23: #   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\\n24: #...\n  Line 13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830160398,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_8GYvZEQ9rdhOqsDDSgQY7raf\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":800},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n2: # DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (CONFIRM MODE)\\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n4: # Same workflow as deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml, with user approval\\n5: # gates at init, before each parallel sweep, and before synthesis.\\n6: #\\n7: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\\n8: # - Flow control is branch-label-driven (on_resume / on_fresh / on_A...);\\n9: #   `when:` is reserved for future typed predicates. See\\n10: #   `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`.\\n11: #\\n12: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\\n13: # - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH (iteration-NNN.md + JSONL appends), classified\\n14: #   write-path below so Gate 3 trigger extraction surfaces it.\\n15: #\\n16: # HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\\n17: # - Every seat is a READ-ONLY analyzer returning structured findings; the\\n18: #   HOST is the ONLY writer of merged state (iterations, coverage-graph,\\n19: #   dashboard, Context Report). Gate-3-safe even with permissive CLI sandboxes.\\n20: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n21: role: Deep Context Loop Manager\\n22: purpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection and user approval gates\\n23: action: Run deep-context loop with user confirmation at each phase t...\n  Line 16: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830176170,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_ADX8Yj26bE4CaW7M0xcCY62v\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"git show --no-ext-diff --unified=80 -- '.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md'\",\"timeout\":120000,\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\",\"description\":\"Shows committed diff for reviewed command\"},\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"metadata\":{\"output\":\"(no output)\",\"exit\":0,\"description\":\"Shows committed diff for reviewed command\",\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"Shows committed diff for reviewed command\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780830176138,\"end\":1780830176168}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_08faf851985af1e6016a254fdefc0081918ee8f0ac630e9bb1\"}},\"id\":\"prt_ea1bfff12001mD8J1sMejDYJTh\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"messageID\":\"msg_ea1bfc9160013TWMcH8b6U6Rr5\"}}\n\n  Line 19: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830181117,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4d5ffez2b7k3bQf6joyU\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_niIBfrkMctL5vrgerlDPSuPd\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"git show --no-ext-diff --unified=80 531dd53028 -- '.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md'\",\"timeout\":120000,\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\",\"description\":\"Shows target commit diff for command\"},\"output\":\"commit 531dd5302801968a3863e1e5dc90643c790a5cc7\\nAuthor: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\\nDate:   Sun Jun 7 12:23:53 2026 +0200\\n\\n    feat(deep-context): native-only default pool + runtime agent mirrors; hard-blocker gates on all deep commands\\n    \\n    Part A - deep-context native-only default pool (specs 134/005, 134/006):\\n    - Add .claude/agents/deep-context.md + .codex/agents/deep-context.toml runtime mirrors\\n      of the canonical .opencode agent (it was the only deep-loop agent missing them, so\\n      native seats silently failed to dispatch from Claude Code / Codex)\\n    - Default fanout.executors to 2 native; restructure the pool question to\\n      A) Native only (default) / B) Custom; de-name the heterogeneous pool everywhere it\\n      read as the default (command, YAMLs, SKILL, README); soften the agent body\\n    - Document the canonical-source + runtime-mirror convention in deep-context and\\n      deep-loop-runtime SKILL.md\\n    \\n    Part B - deep-command hard-blocker gates (spec 136):\\n    - Add the Phase 0 @general-agent verification block to the 5 deep commands that lacked\\n      it (context, research, review, ask-ai-council, skill-benchmark)\\n    - Ensure every deep command opens with two ordered HARD-BLOCK gates: Phase 0 then a\\n      BLOCKED setup phase (STOP/wait in :confirm, fail-fast in :auto); fix the\\n      model-benchmark display box\\n    \\n    Validated: validate.sh --strict passes for 134/005, 134/006, and 136.\\n    \\n    Co-Autho...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/134-deep-context-gathering/review/seats/seat-08.json:\n  Line 2: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830078636,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4bcffewn4EkXFcDL2C0w\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_DZ33z10MtoyrL78k2sv5sUf5\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: description: \\\"Benchmark a model or prompt framework: fixtures, pattern or 5dim scoring, deterministic or graded runs. :auto/:confirm.\\\"\\n3: argument-hint: \\\"<profile_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--scorer=pattern|5dim] [--grader=noop|mock|llm] [--iterations=N] [--executor=NAME --model=NAME] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL - READ FIRST**\\n8: >\\n9: > This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\\n10: >\\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\\n12: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\\n13: > 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\\n14: > 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\\n15: > 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\\n16: >\\n17: > This command is **general-agent based** - orchestrates deep-improvement skill invocation in model-benchmark mode.\\n18: > This command is the dedicated Lane B entry. It sets `lane = model-benchmark` directly. It does NOT ask a lane question.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: # 🚨 PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\\n23: \\n24: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\\n25: \\n26: ```\\n27: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\\n28: \\n29: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\\n30: │\\n31: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\\n...\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830078668,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4bcffewn4EkXFcDL2C0w\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_ft8DSjyV8qmL32vVJh0yPZhw\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: description: \\\"Evaluate and improve any agent: 5 dimensions, proposals, scoring, guarded promotion. :auto/:confirm.\\\"\\n3: argument-hint: \\\"<agent_path> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--iterations=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task\\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**\\n8: >\\n9: > This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\\n10: >\\n11: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**\\n12: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\\n13: > 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs\\n14: > 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)\\n15: > 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute\\n16: >\\n17: > This command is **general-agent based** — orchestrates deep-improvement skill invocation.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: # 🚨 PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\\n22: \\n23: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\\n24: \\n25: ```\\n26: EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\\n27: \\n28: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\\n29: │\\n30: ├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\\n31: │   ├─ You can orchestrate deep-improvement invocation\\n32: │   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\\n33: │   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\\n34: │\\n35: ├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\\n...\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830078684,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4bcffewn4EkXFcDL2C0w\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\"