s_15e41e4bcffewn4EkXFcDL2C0w\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"bash\",\"callID\":\"call_1arFxRahBOBWkeDe5ZoiLsOv\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"python3 - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfor path in ['.opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md','.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md','.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md']:\\n    print(path)\\n    lines=Path(path).read_text().splitlines()\\n    for i,l in enumerate(lines,1):\\n        if '│' in l:\\n            # count visible chars roughly codepoints between first and last box pipe if line starts with spaces then pipe\\n            if l.strip().startswith('│') and l.strip().endswith('│'):\\n                s=l.strip()\\n                print(i, len(s), repr(s))\\n    print()\\nPY\",\"timeout\":120000,\"workdir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\",\"description\":\"Measure box line widths\"},\"output\":\".opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md\\n30 1 '│'\\n35 1 '│'\\n38 1 '│'\\n40 1 '│'\\n42 1 '│'\\n45 65 '│   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │'\\n46 66 '│   │                                                            │'\\n47 66 '│   │ This command orchestrates the deep-improvement skill in    │'\\n48 66 '│   │ model-benchmark mode and runs general-agent based.         │'\\n49 66 '│   │                                                            │'\\n50 66 '│   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │'\\n51 66 '│   │   /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop [arguments]             │'\\n53 1 '│'\\n160 66 '│ **Before proceeding, please answer:**                          │'\\n161 66 '│                                                                │'\\n162 67 '│ **Q0. Benchmark Profile** (if not provided in command):         │'\\n163 68 '│    Which benchmark profile should drive the fixtures?            │'\\n164 74 '│    A) Default - assets/model-benchmark/benc...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/134-deep-context-gathering/review/seats/seat-05.json:\n  Line 2: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090520,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e459ffefL3dD5gIYKuaMD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers\",\"callID\":\"call_1hzhDOMsiu9AUwseJ9V7v44e\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"prompt\":\"Act as a deep-review analyzer. READ-ONLY: do not write, edit, or create any file; return findings ONLY. Review ONLY .opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md focusing on hard-blocker gates: Phase 0 @general block correctness, BLOCKED unified setup phase, EXECUTION PROTOCOL first-action order (Phase 0 then setup), no internal contradictions, restart line. Return JSON only.\",\"specFolder\":\"\",\"tenantId\":\"\",\"userId\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"\",\"limit\":3,\"session_id\":\"\",\"turnNumber\":1,\"include_cognitive\":false},\"output\":\"{\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Matched 3 memories via trigger phrases\\\",\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"matchType\\\": \\\"trigger-phrase\\\",\\n    \\\"count\\\": 3,\\n    \\\"results\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"memoryId\\\": 8680,\\n        \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/023-context-preservation-metrics\\\",\\n        \\\"filePath\\\": \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/023-context-preservation-metrics/spec.md\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Feature Specification: Phase 023 — [system-spec-kit/024-compact-code-graph/023-context-preservation-metrics/spec]\\\",\\n        \\\"matchedPhrases\\\": [\\n          \\\"phase\\\",\\n          \\\"context\\\"\\n        ],\\n        \\\"importanceWeight\\\": 0.8\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"memoryId\\\": 8522,\\n        \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/001-precompact-hook\\\",\\n        \\\"filePath\\\": \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/001-precompact-hook/spec.md\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Phase 1: Compaction Context Injection [system-spec-kit/024-compact-code-graph/001-precompact-hook/spec]\\\",\\n       ...\n  Line 5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830105950,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e459ffefL3dD5gIYKuaMD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"skill\",\"callID\":\"call_BUNBzk3ab5RZZ4MfTFIt7Vxt\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"name\":\"sk-doc\"},\"output\":\"<skill_content name=\\\"sk-doc\\\">\\n# Skill: sk-doc\\n\\n<!-- Keywords: sk-doc, markdown-quality, skill-creation, document-validation, ascii-flowchart, llms-txt, content-optimization, extract-structure -->\\n\\n# Documentation Creation Specialist - Unified Markdown & Component Management\\n\\nUnified specialist providing: (1) Document quality pipeline with structure enforcement and content optimization, (2) OpenCode component creation (skills, agents, commands) with scaffolding, validation and packaging, (3) ASCII flowchart creation for visualizing workflows, (4) Install guide creation for setup documentation and (5) Feature catalog and manual testing playbook creation for inventory and validation packages.\\n\\n**Core Principle**: Structure first, then content, then quality.\\n\\n**Architecture**: Scripts handle deterministic parsing/metrics. AI handles quality judgment and recommendations.\\n\\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n\\n### Use Case: Document Quality Management\\n\\nEnforce markdown structure, optimize content for AI assistants, validate quality through script-assisted AI analysis.\\n\\n**README Creation** - Use `readme_template.md` + `readme_creation.md` when:\\n- Creating new README for any folder or project\\n- User requests \\\"create a README\\\", \\\"add documentation\\\", \\\"write a README\\\"\\n- Folder needs comprehensive documentation\\n- Workflow: [readme_creation.md](./references/readme_creation.md) | Template: [readme_template.md](./assets/readme/readme_template.md)\\n\\n**Skill README Creation** - Use `skill_readme_template.md` when:\\n- Creating or refreshing `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md`\\n- A skill README needs human-facing purpose, quick start, structure, examples, troubleshooting, FAQ or related-resource navigation\\n- Template: [skill_readme_temp...\n  Line 8: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830111927,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e459ffefL3dD5gIYKuaMD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_UyxXMfdbKthQdvpVmLsvNwj0\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":400},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: description: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\n3: argument-hint: \\\"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, code_graph_query, code_graph_context\\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: > **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\\n8: \\n9: > **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\\n10: >\\n11: > This command runs a structured YAML workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.\\n12: >\\n13: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\\n14: > 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)\\n15: > 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) in this Markdown entrypoint and resolve:\\n16: >    - `scope`\\n17: >    - `spec_folder`\\n18: >    - `execution_mode`\\n19: >    - `maxIterations`\\n20: >    - `convergenceThreshold`\\n21: >    - `executor_pool` (shared-scope pool; native-only by default)\\n22: > 3. Load the corresponding YAML file from `assets/` only after all setup values are resolved:\\n23: >    - Auto: `deep_start-context-...\n  Line 11: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830118724,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e459ffefL3dD5gIYKuaMD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_kTQGoHEaXcoMO1P3YPYo2kkL\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md\",\"offset\":401,\"limit\":120},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n401: \\n402: ### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\\n403: `ANCHOR:deep-context-[scope]`, `ANCHOR:reuse-catalog`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\\n404: \\n405: ---\\n406: \\n407: ## 7. SKILL REFERENCE\\n408: \\n409: Full protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/deep-context/SKILL.md`\\n410: \\n411: Key references:\\n412: - Loop protocol: `deep-context/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\\n413: - Convergence: `deep-context/references/convergence/convergence.md`\\n414: - Context Report template: `deep-context/assets/context_report_template.md`\\n415: - Config shape + default pool: `deep-context/assets/deep_context_config.json`\\n416: \\n417: Shared runtime: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (coverage-graph `loop_type='context'`, `scripts/convergence.cjs`, `scripts/upsert.cjs`, `scripts/fanout-run.cjs`, `lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs`).\\n418: Per-model prompt framing: `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-small-model/`.\\n419: \\n420: ---\\n421: \\n422: ## 8. EXAMPLES\\n423: \\n424: ```\\n425: # Default native-only pool (2 @deep-context seats sweeping the same scope)\\n426: /deep:start-context-loop:auto \\\"WebSocket reconnection in the realtime client\\\"\\n427: /deep:start-context-loop:confirm \\\"notification template rendering pipeline\\\"\\n428: /deep:start-context-loop:auto \\\"checkout cart merge logic\\\" --max-iterations 6 --convergence 0.10\\n429: \\n430: # Native-only pool, explicit (identical to the default)\\n431: /deep:start-context-loop:auto \\\"auth session refresh\\\" \\\\\\n432:   --executor=nati...\n  Line 14: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830170692,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e459ffefL3dD5gIYKuaMD\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_b7Pa3fe1QtB0a0ZTBJViahlW\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"(:restart|restart|:auto|:confirm|FIRST ACTION|Unified Setup|GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED|STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED)\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 31 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/start-context-loop.md:\\n  Line 2: description: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\\n\\n  Line 3: argument-hint: \\\"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\\\"\\n\\n  Line 13: > **YOUR FIRST ACTION (two HARD-BLOCK gates — do them in order, skip neither):**\\n\\n  Line 15: > 2. Run the Unified Setup Phase (BLOCKED gate) in this Markdown entrypoint and resolve:\\n\\n  Line 27: > This command is **general-agent based** — it orchestrates the deep-context loop. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) below are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\\n\\n  Line 34: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\\n\\n  Line 47: │   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\\n\\n  Line 55:     │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\\n\\n  Line 60:     │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\\n\\n  Line 80: > **Canonical mode syntax:** use attached command suffixes (`/deep:start-context-loop:auto`, `/deep:start-context-loop:confirm`) and keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\\n\\n  Line 92: **FIRST MESSA...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/134-deep-context-gathering/review/seats/seat-09.json:\n  Line 2: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090088,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_4EGWE087JZ25VNBoa4xTUaIw\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":400},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n2: # DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (AUTO MODE)\\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\\n5: # - This asset does not use typed BooleanExpr predicates under `when:`;\\n6: #   flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing notes if needed; `when:` is reserved\\n9: #   for future typed predicates and must NOT carry free-form prose.\\n10: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\\n11: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\\n12: #\\n13: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\\n14: # - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files and\\n15: #   JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as write-path\\n16: #   below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger extraction\\n17: #   surfaces resume correctly rather than false-negative.\\n18: #\\n19: # HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\\n20: # - Every executor seat (native @deep-context subagent or CLI seat) is a\\n21: #   READ-ONLY analyzer that returns structured findings. The HOST (this\\n22: #   workflow) is the ONLY writer of merged state: iteration files,\\n23: #   coverage-graph, dashboard, and the Context Report. This keeps the loop\\n24: #...\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090155,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_LPB8SvV5Y6dHxr7dg4PgDU8c\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":400},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n2: # DEEP CONTEXT: ITERATIVE CODEBASE-CONTEXT LOOP (CONFIRM MODE)\\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n4: # Same workflow as deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml, with user approval\\n5: # gates at init, before each parallel sweep, and before synthesis.\\n6: #\\n7: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT:\\n8: # - Flow control is branch-label-driven (on_resume / on_fresh / on_A...);\\n9: #   `when:` is reserved for future typed predicates. See\\n10: #   `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`.\\n11: #\\n12: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION:\\n13: # - `resume` is a WRITE-PATH (iteration-NNN.md + JSONL appends), classified\\n14: #   write-path below so Gate 3 trigger extraction surfaces it.\\n15: #\\n16: # HOST-WRITES-STATE CONTRACT (deep-context invariant):\\n17: # - Every seat is a READ-ONLY analyzer returning structured findings; the\\n18: #   HOST is the ONLY writer of merged state (iterations, coverage-graph,\\n19: #   dashboard, Context Report). Gate-3-safe even with permissive CLI sandboxes.\\n20: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n21: role: Deep Context Loop Manager\\n22: purpose: Iterative codebase-context gathering via parallel heterogeneous sweeps with convergence detection and user approval gates\\n23: action: Run deep-context loop with user confirmation at each phase t...\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090199,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_uhW8opJzaZX4bp8HuKQ2447s\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/SKILL.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-context\\n3: description: \\\"Iterative codebase-context-gathering deep loop. Runs a configurable pool over a shared scope in parallel (native-only by default; optional heterogeneous CLI seats) and synthesizes a reuse-first Context Report for planning/implementation. Use before /speckit:plan or /speckit:implement to map existing code, integration points, and conventions.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 1.2.0\\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: <!-- Keywords: deep-context, context-gathering, codebase-context, reuse-catalog, by-model-parallel-sweep, agreement-merge, convergence-detection, coverage-graph, context-report, heterogeneous-executor-pool, pre-planning-context, relevance-gated-coverage -->\\n9: \\n10: # Deep Context\\n11: \\n12: Iterative, multi-model **codebase-context-gathering** loop. It sweeps the existing repository for the code relevant to a feature and synthesizes an implementation/planning-ready **Context Report** whose highest-value section is a **REUSE catalog** (existing functions/utilities to extend, cited by `file:symbol`). It is the \\\"understand\\\" loop that runs *before* `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:implement`.\\n13: \\n14: It is the fourth deep loop and the third consumer of `deep-loop-runtime` (alongside `deep-research` and `deep-review`). Unlike them it is **inward** (the codebase, not the web), and unlike a one-shot context lookup it is **convergence-gated** and **multi-model**: an operator-composed pool of e...\n  Line 5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090203,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_ZQxe1OMMkeITaEqrft97nEx6\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/README.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-context/README.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: \\\"deep-context: Heterogeneous Codebase Context Loop\\\"\\n3: description: \\\"Iterative, multi-model context-gathering loop that maps existing code for reuse, integration points, and conventions before planning or implementation.\\\"\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"gather context for feature\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"map the code for X\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"what existing code can I reuse\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"deep context loop\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"pre-plan context sweep\\\"\\n10: ---\\n11: \\n12: # deep-context\\n13: \\n14: Iterative, multi-model codebase-context-gathering loop that sweeps the existing repository for the code relevant to a feature and synthesizes a reuse-first Context Report before planning or implementation.\\n15: \\n16: ---\\n17: \\n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n19: \\n20: ### Purpose\\n21: \\n22: `deep-context` maps existing code so that `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:implement` start from verified knowledge of what to reuse, where to connect, and which conventions to follow — rather than ad-hoc exploration. It runs a heterogeneous pool of executors over the same code scope in parallel and uses cross-executor **agreement** to rank findings by confidence.\\n23: \\n24: ### Usage\\n25: \\n26: Use this README for human orientation: command examples, packet layout, configuration, usage scenarios, troubleshooting, and reference navigation. Use `SKILL.md` for runtime instructions and smart routing.\\n27: \\n28: ### Key Statistics\\n29: \\n30: | Metric | Value |\\n31: |---|---|\\n32: | Version | `1.0.0` |\\n33: | Primary ...\n  Line 6: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830090203,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_DiDjFovZwZEVGAJeQCmb73DE\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-loop-runtime\\n3: version: 1.4.0\\n4: description: \\\"Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing.\\\"\\n5: allowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: # Deep Loop Runtime\\n9: \\n10: Shared runtime infrastructure for the deep-review and deep-research loop workflows. The FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation moved the shared runtime libraries, coverage-graph ownership, script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests into this peer skill.\\n11: \\n12: ---\\n13: \\n14: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n15: \\n16: This skill is consumed by deep-review and deep-research workflow YAML and script paths, not invoked directly as a user-facing workflow.\\n17: \\n18: Use it when a deep-loop workflow needs shared runtime support for:\\n19: \\n20: - executor configuration and audit metadata\\n21: - prompt-pack rendering\\n22: - post-dispatch validation\\n23: - atomic state files and JSONL repair\\n24: - loop locking and permissions gates\\n25: - Bayesian scoring and fallback routing\\n26: - coverage-graph schema, query, and signal interpretation\\n27: \\n28: ### Activation Triggers\\n29: \\n30: This skill is activated when:\\n31: \\n32: - A deep-review or deep-research workflow YAML invokes `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<name>.cjs`\\n33: - A test file imports `from '.../deep-loop-runtime/lib/...'`\\n34: - An operator queries / mutates the coverage graph via the runtime scr...\n  Line 9: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830096448,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_HRvXYTL97NK90SvInhJaPtAR\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml\",\"offset\":401,\"limit\":500},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n401: \\n402:           step_sweep_cli_pool:\\n403:             description: \\\"Dispatch ALL CLI seats as ONE-SHOT analysis seats over the SHARED focus, in parallel\\\"\\n404:             skip_when: \\\"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\\\"\\n405:             dispatch_mode: one_shot_analysis_council\\n406:             critical: |\\n407:               ONE-SHOT-ANALYSIS REQUIREMENT (by-model shared scope): each CLI seat performs exactly ONE\\n408:               read-only analysis pass over the SHARED current_focus this iteration — identical to a native\\n409:               seat, just a different model lens. A CLI seat does NOT run its own loop. Use the council\\n410:               parallel scaffold, NOT the autonomous-lineage runner, for the per-iteration sweep.\\n411:             primary:\\n412:               tool: \\\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs#dispatchCouncilSeats\\\"\\n413:               note: |\\n414:                 Orchestrate the CLI seats from the Node host via the council scaffold:\\n415:                   dispatchCouncilSeats({ roundId, seats, dispatchSeat, context })\\n416:                 fans the seats out with Promise.all and aggregates per-seat results (fulfilled/rejected +\\n417:                 duration). roundId = \\\"iter-{current_iteration}\\\". seats = config.fanout.executors filtered to\\n418:                 kind != 'native', each carrying its rendered promp...\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830096453,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4beffeUH8qiOdza8m13l\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_m3dUBeC0UGIlC6RpcwBJlZ22\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml\",\"offset\":401,\"limit\":500},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-context-loop_confirm.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n401: \\n402:       step_parallel_sweep:\\n403:         action: \\\"Dispatch the WHOLE pool over the SHARED current focus CONCURRENTLY; barrier-join\\\"\\n404:         note: |\\n405:           This is the defining step. The native batch AND the CLI pool start TOGETHER (true\\n406:           heterogeneous parallelism: 2 native + N CLI all at once) and the host waits for ALL\\n407:           seats before merging. Both sub-steps are launched WITHOUT waiting for each other.\\n408:         launch_together: [step_sweep_native_batch, step_sweep_cli_pool]\\n409:         barrier_join: \\\"Wait for BOTH step_sweep_native_batch AND step_sweep_cli_pool to settle before step_merge_findings\\\"\\n410:         sub_steps:\\n411: \\n412:           step_sweep_native_batch:\\n413:             description: \\\"Dispatch ALL native seats as a SINGLE PARALLEL BATCH (one parallel batch, NOT a sequential for_each)\\\"\\n414:             skip_when: \\\"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\\\"\\n415:             dispatch_mode: parallel_batch\\n416:             critical: |\\n417:               NATIVE-PARALLEL REQUIREMENT: emit ALL native @deep-context Task dispatches in ONE batch\\n418:               (a single set of concurrent Task calls), NOT one-at-a-time in a loop. Each native seat\\n419:               gets the SAME current_focus and its own rendered prompt. Read-only analyzers.\\n420:             batch:\\n421:               for_each_native_seat: ...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/134-deep-context-gathering/review/seats/seat-02.json:\n  Line 2: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830076758,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4baffeWdGn5hg9VtE2Ze\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_sPpCzcnnsKC5EnOLo9KX2Wb4\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.codex/agents/deep-context.toml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":4000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.codex/agents/deep-context.toml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Agent: deep-context\\n2: # Converted from: .opencode/agents/deep-context.md\\n3: #\\n4: # code_graph_query / code_graph_context reach Codex through the shared MCP\\n5: # server registration (same channel as other deep-loop tools); no explicit\\n6: # TOML tool whitelist is required for availability. (Same note as deep-research.toml.)\\n7: name = \\\"deep-context\\\"\\n8: description = \\\"LEAF read-only deep-context analyzer seat: one parallel sweep of a slice, returns a reuse-first finding set.\\\"\\n9: sandbox_mode = \\\"read-only\\\"\\n10: model = \\\"gpt-5.4\\\"\\n11: model_reasoning_effort = \\\"high\\\"\\n12: \\n13: developer_instructions = '''\\n14: # The Deep Context Analyzer: Read-Only Seat\\n15: \\n16: Executes ONE read-only analysis sweep of an assigned code slice within a heterogeneous parallel pool, then RETURNS a structured, reuse-first finding set as its final message. It is the native counterpart to the cli-* analyzer seats; it gathers and reports context but writes nothing.\\n17: \\n18: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\\n19: \\n20: \\n21: **CRITICAL**: This agent is a READ-ONLY analyzer SEAT, not the loop. It NEVER writes files. The host (`/deep:start-context-loop`) writes every iteration file, the coverage-graph, and the merged Context Report. This seat's entire deliverable is the structured finding set it returns in stdout.\\n22: \\n23: **IMPORTANT**: This agent is one member of a shared-scope agreement pool. Multiple seats (native, and op...\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780830076780,\"sessionID\":\"ses_15e41e4baffeWdGn5hg9VtE2Ze\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"too